When the old penalty of death had (at least in the case of political offences) eeased to be imposed³ by sentence of the iudicia populi, the Romans did not introduce an equivalent punishment in its place, but determined in a legislative form⁴ the penalties for the several offences according to the merits of the cases as they arose.
